column1: The most famous monument in the world allows one to identify all the unintentional monuments in the '' rubble '' of the everyday functional environment :  In the name of the Acropolis , this wall surrounding a pasture seems noble to us and we appreciate the meaning of its line ; this haystack , alive and throbbing with the caress of peasant hands , rises like a monument from the rubble ... in a word , these constructions informed with spirit are transposed from the level of utility to the level of mentality : speeches , words striking to the very center of our sensitivity.
